import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['temperature'], data['pressure'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_ylabel('Pressure')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temperature'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['temperature'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pressure'] = pd.to_numeric(data['pressure'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['pressure'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pressure', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['pressure'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['pressure'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Pressure')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of pressure?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wind', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['wind'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['wind'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['wind'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['wind'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Wind')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of wind?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.set_index('date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['temperature'], label='Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['pressure'], label='Pressure')
    ax.plot(data['wind'], label='Wind')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Value')
    ax.set_title('What is the average temperature, pressure, and wind speed over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
